<br>
I was stressed out when people were freaking out about sbs and the nerfs.  I was then 43.<br>
<br>
I thought omg I have invested all my time in this character and they just destroyed it.  Look all these people are leaving the game.  Geeze I have to reroll again.  (I had a hunter that I got to 37 before they really did  destroy those).<br>
<br>
I am now a lvl 50 sb and having lots of fun.  Do I win every fight against Infs..No.  In fact I lose a few more than I win I think.  I attribute it to the fact that I only have like 75k in rps, I don't have a buff bot (I will get one if they aren't nerfed soon)  and I am still learning.<br>
<br>
Do I think things are entirely balanced among the rogues.  I honestly dont.  I think that steppin razor is absolutely right on his quest to get dragonfang switched to a second step off evade change move.  I think that infs have so many spec points that they get an advantage.  For example, if the new poisons are only lvl 50.  I can't use em.  Every Inf will get them and they are even better than lifebane.   <br>
<br>
I hope that mythic addresses these issues.  However, above all things I am having so much fun right now.  I go out in teams of rogues and we generally do fine.  I don't solo but then I rarely face a solo inf that is not uber buffbotted.<br>
<br>
So don't stress it so much.<br>
<br>
Enjoy the game.<br>
