<br>
With this patch every Nightshade will be 30% better versus SB's due to armor resist changes going from 15% vulnm to 15% resist. Spec blades for a 15% bonus and you now have a 45% bonus versus SB's as a Blades NS.<br>
<br>
Every infiltrator will be 15% better due to armor changes going from 15% vuln to neutral. Spec Slash instead of thrust and you have a 30% bonus to SB's.<br>
<br>
You will say &quot;But now you have a bonus to scale and are neutral to other armors&quot;.  Sorry, this doesn't cut it. You, as NS and Infiltrators, always had the option of speccing a skill that gives you a bonus to Mid healers and Viking Classes. There is no way a SB can go toe to toe with a Hero or Armsman. I thought everyone said Assasssins were to hunt other Assassins, Casters, and Archers? Now we, as SB's, are out of the Assassin hunting game.<br>
<br>
Now to a major complaint all Nightshades have.  Nightshades are complaining that they start with races that have base 40 con and have a substantial lessened number of hit points then SB's. then I look at page one of this thread and see: <br>
<br>
&quot;My weapon skill tips 1150 with a certain Druid's buffs, my hitpoints go from 1096 to 1600. Whenever I can get them I do. <br>
<br>
<br>
Balor Gafdan Nightshade of Guinivere&quot;<br>
<br>
As a Norse SB starting with 70 con I have, with my epic armor and items, 127 con.  I have 1159 hitpoints.  I have 63 MORE HP  then Balor the Nightshade. Every Nightshade can get to his approximate con level. So where are these 300-400 HP's difference that Nightshades complain about?<br>
<br>
Where is my Shadowblade Uberness versus other Assassins that all these people complain about?  <br>
<br>
Left Ax was nerfed and now needs a load of spec points put into it to be a viable skill while in contrast NS/Inf get CD/DW where with 0 spec at level 50 they get a 37.5% boost to melee power.  <br>
<br>
The one shot coming unstealthed hurt Critblades a lot and Epic armor pretty much stopped one shots, although they still do occur infrequently.<br>
<br>
2 handed weapons get a 15% damage increase over 1 handed weapons. So if I use a 2 hander I will be an assassin to be feared by other Assassins? maybe for the perf , if you can get it in on another Assassin but with the evades that happen to slow swinging 2 handed weapons you are crazy to use one in an Assassin versus Assassin fight.<br>
<br>
Infiltrators 453 Spec points versus 40-50 Hp Increase? I just have shown up above that the HP difference between SB's (at least me and Balor) and NS are very negligable. Imagine how much less they are to Saracens and Britons who have 10 and 20 more con to start with then NS.<br>
<br>
Dragonfang? Quite a weapon skill. <br>
<br>
Viper and Vanish versus Shadowrun? Shadowrun is worthless compared to the other 2.<br>
<br>
Slash as the only weapon damage type available to SB's while the other Assassins can spec Thrust or Slash.<br>
<br>
Now the Armor Resists in this patch hammer SB's mercilessly while giving big boosts to NS and Infiltrators.<br>
<br>
So SB's don't have anything to complain about?<br>
<br>
On the contrary, we have quite a lot to complain about.<br>
<br>
Infiltrator&gt;NS&gt;&gt;SB with the new patch.<br>
<br>
